examples.text: Kaç yıl oldu saymadım köyden göçeli
examples.translation: I haven't counted how many years it’s been since I left the village

glosses: to get married to a man

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish كوچمك (göçmek, “to migrate”), from Old Anatolian Turkish كوچمك (göçmek), from Proto-Turkic *köč- (“to migrate”). Cognate of Azerbaijani köçmək, Kazakh көшу (köşu), and Karakhanid كُجْماكْ (köčmēk).
